'''Mike Peterson Maignan''' ({{IPA|fr|mɛɲɑ̃}}; born 3 July 1995) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Goalkeeper (association football)|goalkeeper]] for {{Italian football updater|Milan}} club [[AC Milan]], which he captains, and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

Maignan came through the [[Paris Saint-Germain FC Youth Academy|youth teams]] at [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]], where he often served as an unused substitute. In 2015 he joined [[Lille OSC|Lille]] for €1 million, and became their first-choice in 2017. He was voted [[Ligue 1]]'s [[Trophées UNFP du football#Goalkeeper of the Year|goalkeeper of the year]] in [[2018–19 Ligue 1|2018–19]], and won the league title in [[2020–21 Ligue 1|2020–21]]. He then moved to [[AC Milan]] for €15 million, winning [[Serie A]] in his [[2021–22 Serie A|first season]] and making the Team of the Season.

After earning 37 caps for France at youth level, Maignan made his senior international debut in 2020. He was selected in the French squads for [[UEFA Euro 2020]] and [[UEFA Euro 2024|Euro 2024]].

==Early life==
Mike Peterson Maignan<ref>{{cite web |url=https://editorial.uefa.com/resources/028a-1a4bb1ff59a1-9bf04f81cbcf-1000/uel_booking_list_before_round_of_16_1st_leg.pdf |title=UEFA Europa League 2023/2024: Booking List before Round of 16, 1st leg |publisher=UEFA |page=7 |date=29 February 2024 |access-date=26 August 2024}}</ref> was born on 3 July 1995<ref name="Soccerway"/> in [[Cayenne]], French Guiana, to a Haitian mother born in [[Aquin]] and a Guadeloupean father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lepopulaire.fr/limousin/sports/actualite/football/2012/11/03/rencontre-avec-le-portier-de-lequipe-de-france_1319682.html |title=Rencontre avec le portier de l'équipe de France |trans-title=Meeting with the France national team goalkeeper|editor=Kao, Kevin |date=11 March 2012 |publisher=Le Populaire |accessdate=25 July 2015|language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://cjsscayes.com/|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725191616/http://cjsscayes.com/?p=2561|url-status=usurped|title=澳亚国际 - 澳亚国际在线登录 - 开户注册中心|archivedate=25 July 2015|website=澳亚国际 - 澳亚国际在线登录 - 开户注册中心}}</ref> He grew up in [[Villiers-le-Bel]], in the northern suburbs of Paris.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Tassel |first=Victor |date=2019-11-21 |title=Villiers-le-Bel : Mike Maignan, le footballeur qui fait «la fierté des Carreaux» |url=https://www.leparisien.fr/val-d-oise-95/villiers-le-bel-mike-maignan-la-fierte-des-carreaux-21-11-2019-8198589.php |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=leparisien.fr |language=fr-FR}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Paris Saint-Germain===
Maignan played in the lower categories of [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] before being promoted in 2013 to the first team. He participated in the [[2013&ndash;14 UEFA Youth League]] in which his team reached the quarter-finals, being eliminated by [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/uefayouthleague/news/0253-0d041325706e-22c4ed2e158e-1000--sanchez-heads-madrid-into-semi-finals/ |title=Sánchez heads Madrid into semi-finals |editor=Burke, Chris |date=11 March 2014 |publisher=UEFA |access-date=25 July 2015}}</ref>

In June 2013 Maignan signed his first professional contract, of three years.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ponchelet |first1=David |title=Le Guyanais Mike Maignan signe avec le Paris Saint Germain! |trans-title=French Guianese Mike Maignan signs with Paris Saint-Germain!|url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/2013/06/06/le-guyanais-mike-maignan-signe-avec-le-paris-saint-germain-39957.html |accessdate=9 October 2019 |publisher=La 1ere |date=6 June 2013 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Kundzelevicius |first=Paulius |date=2021-06-04 |title=Player Analysis: Mike Maignan, the New Milan Goalkeeper |url=https://cultofcalcio.com/player-analysis-mike-maignan-the-new-milan-goalkeeper/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=The Cult of Calcio |language=en-US}}</ref> On 18 December, he was in a matchday squad for the first time, sitting on the bench for [[Nicolas Douchez]] in a 2–1 win over [[AS Saint-Étienne|Saint-Étienne]] in the last 16 of the [[Coupe de la Ligue]].<ref>{{cite news |title=PSG: cinq absents de marque face à Saint-Étienne|trans-title=PSG: five big absences against Saint-Étienne |url=https://www.football365.fr/psg-cinq-absents-de-marque-face-a-saint-etienne-1975415.html |accessdate=9 October 2019 |publisher=Football 365 |date=17 December 2013 |language=French}}</ref> On 19 January 2014 he was included in a [[Ligue 1]] game for the first time, remaining unused as [[Salvatore Sirigu]] played in a 5–0 win over [[FC Nantes|Nantes]] at the [[Parc des Princes]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2014-01-19 |title=Paris Saint Germain 5-0 Nantes |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/25717713 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref>

===Lille===
[[File:Chelsea 2 Lille 1 (49202948728) Mike Maignan.jpg|thumb|left|upright=0.65|Maignan playing for [[Lille OSC|Lille]] in 2019]]

In August 2015, Maignan transferred to fellow Ligue 1 club [[Lille OSC|Lille]] for €1 million on a five-year deal.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mike Maignan : Le Haïtien à Lille pour 5 ans |trans-title=Mike Maignan: Haitian to Lille for five years|url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2015/08/19/mike-maignan-le-haitien-a-lille-pour-5-ans/ |accessdate=9 October 2019 |publisher=Africa Top Sports |date=19 August 2015 |language=French}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |author=The Athletic Staff |date=2021-05-28 |title=AC Milan sign goalkeeper Mike Maignan from Lille |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4211426/2021/05/27/ac-milan-sign-goalkeeper-mike-maignan-from-lille/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref> He made his professional debut on 18 September in a 1–1 draw at [[Stade Rennais F.C.|Rennes]], as a substitute for [[Yassine Benzia]] after [[Vincent Enyeama]] was sent off in the 69th minute. With his first touch, he saved the penalty from [[Paul-Georges Ntep]]; however, in five minutes, he conceded a goal from the same player.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Rennes 1-1 Lille (19 Sep, 2015) Game Analysis - ESPN (AU) |url=https://www.espn.com.au/football/report?gameId=424686 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN |language=en}}</ref>

At the start of the 2017–18 season, manager [[Marcelo Bielsa]] dropped the experienced Enyeama for Maignan. In the second game of the season, a 3–0 loss at [[RC Strasbourg Alsace|Strasbourg]], he was sent off for throwing the ball at an opponent and striker [[Nicolas de Préville]] had to go in goal for the final minutes.<ref>{{Cite news |last=White |first=Adam |last2=Devin |first2=Eric |date=2017-09-25 |title=Marcelo Bielsa loses his cool as Lille's season goes from bad to worse |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2017/sep/25/marcelo-bielsa-lille-monaco-ligue-1 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> The following season, he was an ever-present as Lille finished as runners-up to PSG, and was elected Goalkeeper of the year in the [[Trophées UNFP du football]]. His record was 30 goals conceded, 17 clean sheets, 233 saves and three penalties saved.<ref name=unfp>{{cite news |last1=Noé |first1=Sébastien |title=Trophées UNFP : Élu gardien de l'année, Mike Maignan dans le grand monde |trans-title=Trophées UNFP : Voted goalkeeper of the year, Mike Maignan in the big world|url=https://www.lavoixdunord.fr/585618/article/2019-05-19/mike-maignan-elu-meilleur-gardien-de-l-annee |accessdate=9 October 2019 |newspaper=La Voix du Nord |date=19 May 2019 |language=French}}</ref> In 2020–21, Maignan won the Ligue 1 title, beating his former club PSG on the final day by one point.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-05-24 |title=Ligue 1: How Lille pulled off a shock title triumph - to leave PSG searching for answers |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/57224119 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Maignan finished the season with 21 clean sheets, one short of the league record.<ref>{{Cite news |last=White |first=Adam |last2=Devin |first2=Eric |date=2021-05-24 |title=Lille hold their nerve to clinch their first Ligue 1 title for a decade |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2021/may/24/lille-ligue-1-title-decade-christophe-galtier |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref>

===AC Milan===
[[File:Maignan_1_Milan_2022.jpg|thumb|Maignan playing for [[AC Milan]] in 2022]]

On 27 May 2021, Maignan agreed to sign for [[Serie A]] club [[AC Milan]] on a five-year contract,<ref>{{Cite web |date=27 May 2021 |title=Official Statement: Mike Maignan |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2021-05-27/official-statement-mike-maignan |access-date=27 May 2021 |publisher=[[AC Milan]] |language=en}}</ref> effective from 1 July.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-05-27 |title=AC Milan sign Lille's Mike Maignan to replace Gianluigi Donnarumma |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/57272615 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2025-04-04 |title=Maignan has signed a 5-year contract with Milan, the goalkeeper arrives from Lille on a €13m + €2m bonuses deal |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/maignan-has-signed-a-5-year-contract-with-milan-the-goalkeeper-arrives-from-lille-on-a-13m-2m-bonuses-deal-33070261 |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref> He arrived for a reported fee of €15 million, as a replacement for PSG-bound [[Gianluigi Donnarumma]].<ref>{{Cite news |title=AC Milan land Lille goalkeeper Maignan on five-year deal |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/ac-milan-land-lille-goalkeeper-maignan-on-five-year-deal-997880 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241203124357/https://www.besoccer.com/new/ac-milan-land-lille-goalkeeper-maignan-on-five-year-deal-997880 |archive-date=2024-12-03 |access-date=2025-04-05 |publisher=Be Soccer |language=en}}</ref> He made his debut on 23 August, a 1–0 win at [[U.C. Sampdoria|Sampdoria]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Soccer-Early Diaz strike gets Milan off to winning start |url=https://www.reuters.com/article/uk-soccer-italy-sam-mil-report-idUKKBN2FO1VP |access-date=6 September 2021 |publisher=Reuters |date=23 August 2021}}</ref> On 19 September, in a league match against [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], Maignan was the victim of verbal racial abuse by a Juventus supporter; he responded by calling himself "black and proud".<ref>{{Cite web |date=2021-09-21 |title='Black and proud': Milan's Maignan speaks out as Juve probe racist abuse |url=https://www.france24.com/en/live-news/20210921-black-and-proud-milan-s-maignan-speaks-out-as-juve-probe-racist-abuse |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=France 24 |language=en}}</ref> The supporter was later identified and reported to police, and expelled from the Juventus Club Castagnaro fan club.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Mike Maignan: Juventus fan alleged to have abused AC Milan goalkeeper identified and reported to police |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11863/12415405/mike-maignan-juventus-fan-alleged-to-have-abused-ac-milan-goalkeeper-identified-and-reported-to-police |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241203124032/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11863/12415405/mike-maignan-juventus-fan-alleged-to-have-abused-ac-milan-goalkeeper-identified-and-reported-to-police |archive-date=2024-12-03 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 13 October 2021, Maignan underwent surgery to his left wrist injury and he was expected to be out of action for ten weeks,<ref>{{Cite news |date=2021-10-13 |title=AC Milan keeper Mike Maignan faces 10 weeks out after wrist surgery |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/football/top-stories/ac-milan-keeper-mike-maignan-faces-10-weeks-out-after-wrist-surgery/articleshow/86999824.cms |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The Times of India |issn=0971-8257}}</ref> but returned to the field after six  weeks.<ref>{{Cite web |last=petrosilli |first=Alberto |date=2021-11-28 |title=Milan Sassuolo, Maignan torna titolare: per il francese recupero record |url=https://www.milannews24.com/milan-sassuolo-quindicesima-giornata-serie-a-2021-2022-maignan-titolare/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |language=it-IT}}</ref> He made crucial saves against [[Inter Milan|Inter]], to help his team win a narrow 2–1 [[Derby della Madonnina|derby]] on 5 February.<ref>{{cite news |title=Maignan, il retroscena col posteggiatore prima del derby Inter-Milan|trans-title=Maignan, the background with the valet before the Inter-Milan derby |url=https://sport.sky.it/calcio/serie-a/2022/02/06/maignan-derby-san-siro-casa-milan |access-date=15 February 2022 |publisher=[[Sky Sport (Italy)|Sky Sport]] |date=6 February 2022}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Marcotti |first=Gabriele |date=2022-02-07 |title=Giroud, Milan blow Serie A race wide open, Barcelona thump Atletico Madrid, Senegal win AFCON |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/37625294/giroud-milan-blow-serie-race-wide-open-barcelona-thump-atletico-madrid-senegal-win-afcon |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> Eight days later, he [[assist (association football)|assisted]] [[Rafael Leão]]'s goal in a 1–0 win against Sampdoria, being the first assist made by an AC Milan goalkeeper in Serie A since [[Dida (footballer, born 1973)|Dida]] in 2006.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2022-02-14 |title=CM: Maignan channels Dida, cuts Samp in half again and proves Berlusconi right |url=https://sempremilan.com/mike-maignan-dida-sampdoria-berlusconi |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=SempreMilan |language=en}}</ref> Maignan was awarded the trophy for Best Goalkeeper in Serie A ahead of the last match of the season on 22 May 2022.<ref>{{cite web |title=MVP Serie A 2021/2022 - Maignan awarded as Best Goalkeeper |url=https://www.legaseriea.it/en/press/news/info/mvp-serie-a-2021-2022-maignan-awarded-as-best-goalkeeper |access-date=22 May 2022 |publisher=Serie A |archive-date=30 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220530052424/https://www.legaseriea.it/en/press/news/info/mvp-serie-a-2021-2022-maignan-awarded-as-best-goalkeeper |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Heyes |first=Apollo |date=2022-05-20 |title=Maignan wins Serie A Best Goalkeeper award - Football Italia |url=https://football-italia.net/maignan-wins-serie-a-best-goalkeeper-award/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |website=football-italia.net |language=en-GB}}</ref> Milan won the game 3–0 away to [[U.S. Sassuolo Calcio|Sassuolo]] for their first league title since 2011; it was his record 17th clean sheet of the season.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Del Vecchio |first1=Manuel |title=Milan, Maignan è il portiere con più clean sheet. La Serie A: "Un'aquila"|trans-title=Milan, Maignan is the goalkeeper with the most clean sheets. Serie A: "An eagle" |url=https://www.milannews.it/news/milan-maignan-e-il-portiere-con-piu-clean-sheet-la-serie-a-un-aquila-453682 |access-date=25 June 2022 |publisher=Milan News |date=30 May 2022 |language=Italian}}</ref>

On 18 April 2023, Maignan saved a penalty from [[Khvicha Kvaratskhelia]] during a 1–1 away draw against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]] in the [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League]] quarter-final second leg, which helped his team to qualify to the semi-final, by winning 2–1 on aggregate, for the first time since the 2006–07 season.<ref>{{Cite news |last= |date=2023-04-18 |title=Milan hold firm to deny Napoli after Leão's solo run and Maignan's saves |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/apr/18/napoli-milan-champions-league-quarter-final-second-leg-match-report |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The Guardian |language=en-GB |issn=0261-3077}}</ref> On 2 December, he assisted [[Christian Pulisic]]'s goal in a 3–1 win against [[Frosinone Calcio|Frosinone]], making him the only goalkeeper in Europe's top 5 leagues to record an assist in each of the last 3 seasons.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Romano |first=Fabrizio |title=AC Milan's Mike Maignan is the only goalkeeper in Europe's top five leagues to provide an assist in each of the last three seasons. |url=https://twitter.com/FabrizioRomano/status/1731076012115464589?s=20 |access-date=2023-12-03 |website=X (formerly Twitter) |language=en}}</ref>

In January 2024, after Maignan was allegedly [[Racism in association football|racially abused]] by Udinese fans, he and his teammates walked off the pitch.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-20 |title=Udinese 2-3 AC Milan: Mike Maignan and Milan walk off after alleged racist chanting from home fans |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68045160 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Following the incident, Udinese had to play their next game behind closed doors.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-23 |title=Mike Maignan: Udinese must play game behind closed doors after racist abuse |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68070713 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Initially one Udinese fan was banned for life,<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-22 |title=Udinese fan banned for life for racist abuse towards AC Milan goalkeeper Mike Maignan |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68060176 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> before a further four received similar punishments.<ref>{{Cite news |date=2024-01-24 |title=Mike Maignan: Four Udinese fans banned for life by club over racist abuse of AC Milan goalkeeper |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68086367 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> In October 2024, he was named captain of AC Milan, becoming the fifth foreign international to wear the armband for the club.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Campanale |first=Susy |date=19 October 2024 |title=Maignan becomes fifth Milan captain of this troubled campaign |url=https://football-italia.net/maignan-becomes-fifth-milan-captain-campaign/ |access-date=19 October 2024 |publisher=Football Italia |language=en}}</ref> On 31 January 2026, he extended his contract with the club until 2031.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.acmilan.com/en/news/articles/media/2026-01-31/official-statement-mike-maignan |title=OFFICIAL STATEMENT: MIKE MAIGNAN |publisher=AC Milan |date=31 January 2026 }}</ref>

==International career==
Maignan played for France at every level from [[France national under-16 football team|under-16]] to [[France national under-21 football team|under-21]]. He [[Captain (association football)|captained]] the [[France national under-17 football team|under-17]] side at the [[2012 UEFA European Under-17 Championship|2012 European Championship]] in [[Slovenia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.just-football.com/2013/02/photo-shoot-marvellous-maignan-breaks-boca-hearts-al-kass-international-cup/ |title=Photo, Shoot: Marvellous Maignan Breaks Boca Hearts Al-Kass International Cup |editor=F, Jonathan |date=5 February 2013 |publisher=Just Football |accessdate=25 July 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://talentshunter.net/2013/10/31/mike-maignan/ |title=Talents Hunter - Mike Maignan |access-date=25 July 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150725173922/http://talentshunter.net/2013/10/31/mike-maignan/ |archive-date=25 July 2015 |url-status=dead }}</ref> He received his first senior call-up in May 2019, ahead of [[UEFA Euro 2020]] qualifiers against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]] and [[Andorra national football team|Andorra]] and a friendly with [[Bolivia national football team|Bolivia]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Lille goalkeeper Mike Maignan earns France call-up |url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/story/lille-goalkeeper-mike-maignan-earns-france-call-up-052119 |accessdate=9 October 2019 |agency=Associated Press |website=Fox Sports |date=21 May 2019}}</ref> He made his debut on 7 October 2020 as a half-time substitute for [[Steve Mandanda]] in a friendly against [[Ukraine national football team|Ukraine]], which ended as a 7–1 win at the [[Stade de France]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Béal |first1=Xavier |title=France-Ukraine : Première sélection pour Maignan qui remplace Mandanda à la mi-temps|trans-title=France-Ukraine: First cap for Maignan who replaces Mandanda at half time |url=https://www.goal.com/fr/news/france-ukraine-premiere-selection-pour-maignan-qui-remplace/p6pzzzhnwwmt1uwfj7d67i2x7 |accessdate=14 November 2020 |website=Goal.com |date=7 October 2020 |language=French}}</ref> In May 2021, he was called up for the delayed Euro 2020 finals.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Karim Benzema recalled to France squad for Euro 2020 after six-year absence |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12025/12310278/karim-benzema-recalled-to-france-squad-for-euro-2020-after-six-year-absence |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20241007170930/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/12025/12310278/karim-benzema-recalled-to-france-squad-for-euro-2020-after-six-year-absence |archive-date=2024-10-07 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=Sky Sports |language=en-GB}}</ref>

On 6 June 2022, Maignan made his competitive international debut in a 1–1 [[UEFA Nations League]] draw away to [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], conceding a late penalty by [[Andrej Kramarić]].<ref>{{Cite news |date=2022-06-06 |title=Croatia 1-1 France: Les Bleus yet to win in Nations League |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/61709465 |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> Calf injuries in September and October that year ruled him out of the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Maignan unavailable for Milan until January with calf injury |url=https://timesofmalta.com/articles/view/maignan-unavailable-milan-january-calf-injury.989279 |access-date=15 December 2022 |work=The Times of Malta |date=21 October 2022}}</ref>

Following [[Hugo Lloris]]'s retirement from international football in January 2023, Maignan was promoted to first choice goalkeeper for the France national team.<ref>{{Cite news |last=Bosher |first=Luke |date=2023-01-09 |title=France's Hugo Lloris retires from international football |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/4073870/2023/01/09/hugo-lloris-france-retire/ |access-date=2025-04-05 |work=The New York Times |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref>

He was France's starting goalkeeper at [[UEFA Euro 2024]], helping France to the semi-finals of the competition, where they were defeated 2–1 by eventual champions [[Spain national football team|Spain]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Liew |first1=Jonathan |title=Lamine Yamal’s wonder goal leads Spain past France and into Euro 2024 final |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/article/2024/jul/09/spain-france-euro-2024-semi-final-match-report |access-date=14 July 2025 |work=The Guardian |date=9 July 2024}}</ref> Maignan was named to the team of the tournament for his performances.<ref name="EURO 2024 Team of the Tournament"/>

==Style of play==
Nicknamed "[[Magic Mike]]," in the media, Maignan is considered one of the best goalkeepers in the world. He is known in particular for his imposing stature, physical power, positioning, reflexes, shot-stopping, and distribution, as well as his leadership qualities and ability to organise the defence.<ref>{{cite web |date=18 April 2023 |title=How AC Milan's 'Magic' Mike Maignan became the world's best goalkeeper |url=https://www.goal.com/en-gb/lists/milan-magic-mike-maignan-world-best-goalkeeper/blte2f04ab65ab85d06 |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=Goal.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Benge |first=James |date=13 June 2024 |title=Golazo 100 countdown: Kylian Mbappe, Vinicius Jr. top the best men's soccer players in the world list for 2024 |url=https://www.cbssports.com/soccer/news/golazo-100-countdown-kylian-mbappe-vinicius-jr-top-the-best-mens-soccer-players-in-the-world-list-for-2024/ |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=CBS Sports}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=4 June 2024 |title=2024 FC 100: Neuer among best goalkeepers in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/40179269/manuel-neuer-best-goalkeepers-men-soccer |access-date=5 April 2025 |website=ESPN}}</ref><ref name="shadows">{{cite news |last1=Harpur |first1=Charlotte |last2=Horncastle |first2=James |title=How 'Magic Mike' Maignan emerged from the shadows to become France No 1 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/5622241/2024/07/08/mike-maignan-france-euro-2024/ |access-date=14 July 2025 |work=The New York Times |date=15 July 2024}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Mongiardo |first1=Emanuele |title=Maignan è il portiere giusto per sostituire Donnarumma? – Ultimo Uomo |url=https://www.ultimouomo.com/maignan-milan-donnarumma |publisher=www.ultimouomo.com |access-date=14 July 2025 |language=it |date=28 May 2021}}</ref> Moreover, he is adept at saving penalties.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Whitehead |first1=Jacob |title=France should sub off Lloris while England will fear Neuer: the Euro 2020 goalkeepers with the best penalty records |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/2674454/2021/06/26/goalkeepers-best-penalty-record-euro-2020/ |access-date=18 July 2025 |work=The New York Times |date=26 June 2021}}</ref> He is also good at reading the game and coming off his line, which along with his decision-making and ability with the ball at his feet, allows him to function as a [[sweeper-keeper]].<ref name="shadows"/><ref>{{cite news |last1=Twomey |first1=Liam |last2=Harris |first2=Thom |title=The Chelsea goalkeeping conundrum: Would Mike Maignan have represented an upgrade? |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6416236/2025/06/11/chelsea-maignan-milan-france-sanchez-jorgensen-petrovic/ |access-date=14 July 2025 |work=The New York Times |date=11 June 2025}}</ref> Maignan has also been praised in the media for his consistency and decisive performances in important matches. In 2024, [[Brazil national football team|Brazil]] and [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] goalkeeper [[Alisson Becker]] praised Maignan with the following words: "He is physical, quick, he has clean technique. He is very strong. He is one of the best in the world."<ref>{{cite web |title=2025 FC 100: Martinez among best goalkeepers in men's soccer |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/45163202/2025-fc-100-martinez-best-goalkeepers-mens-soccer |publisher=ESPN.com |access-date=14 July 2025 |language=en |date=4 June 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Why Mike Maignan Said No to Chelsea — and What It Means for AC Milan |url=https://football-italia.net/why-maignan-said-no-chelsea-means-for-milan/ |publisher=football-italia.net |access-date=14 July 2025 |date=7 July 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title='I love Italy' - Liverpool goalkeeper Alisson on Milan, Maignan, Chiesa and UCL plan - Football Italia - September 16 latest |url=https://football-italia.net/liverpool-alisson-on-milan-chiesa-maignan-ucl/ |publisher=football-italia.net |access-date=14 July 2025 |date=16 September 2024}}</ref>

